        person("Tomás", "Rodríguez Taborda", email = "torodriguezt@unal.edu.co", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Implements Bayesian quantile regression approaches using the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm 
    and several MCMC methods with observation weights for complex survey designs. The package provides two main 
    functions: 'bqr.svy()' for single quantile estimation using MCMC methods (Asymmetric Laplace, Score, and 
    Approximate), and 'mo.bqr.svy()' for multiple quantile estimation using the EM algorithm. Includes fast C++ 
    implementations using 'Rcpp', 'RcppEigen', and 'RcppArmadillo' for linear algebra, and 'Boost' (via the 
    'BH' package) for special functions such as Bessel. The package also calls 'GIGrvg' for sampling from 
    Generalized Inverse Gaussian distributions. Methods are based on Yu and Moyeed (2001) 
    <doi:10.1016/S0167-7152(01)00124-9> and Kozumi and Kobayashi (2011) <doi:10.1016/j.csda.2011.04.021>.
